# CODEOWNERS. Copy to `.github/CODEOWNERS` (or the repo root).
# Lines map file patterns to owners; the LAST matching pattern wins (like
# .gitignore precedence). When a PR touches a matched path, its owners are
# auto-requested for review. Pair with a ruleset that requires CODEOWNERS
# review on protected branches. Background:
#   ../../references/github/pull-requests.md
#   ../../references/github/branch-protection-and-rulesets.md
#
# Owners are @username or @org/team or an email. Replace the placeholders.

# Default owner for everything not matched more specifically below.
*                       @your-username

# Area-specific owners (examples — delete or adapt):
# /src/api/             @your-org/backend
# /src/ui/              @your-org/frontend
# *.tf                  @your-org/infra
# /.github/             @your-username
# /docs/                @your-org/docs
